    "narrative": "For our April 12th slate, the numbers point clearly to **Daulton Varsho** (72.31) and **Bryson Stott** (68.67) as the cornerstones of the LawDog offense. **Daulton Varsho** benefits significantly from a favorable matchup against Bradley, who is struggling with a 4.45 xERA, and his placement in the #2 hole provides elite RBI/Run potential. Meanwhile, **Bryson Stott** remains a high-floor play against Gallen; his 13% platoon edge and favorable park factor make him our most reliable asset for today\u2019s 5x5 rotation. We are also keeping a close eye on **Taylor Ward** (67.73) and **Brendan Donovan** (66.36), both of whom are projected for strong outputs due to park-factor boosts and advantageous spots in the order against the vulnerable Bolton.\n\nThe most difficult decision on today's bench was keeping **Gleyber Torres** (53.98) out of the lineup. While his base metrics remain solid, the optimizer favored the higher efficiency scores of **Jeremiah Jackson** and **Jonathan Aranda**, as their specific matchup dynamics\u2014particularly the park factors\u2014edged out **Gleyber Torres** by a slim margin in our daily efficiency model. Notably, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** draws a challenging assignment against Sale, resulting in a pedestrian 54.71 score; we are sticking with him due to his ceiling, but the -19% SP skill penalty against an elite arm is a clear risk. Finally, we are monitoring **Cal Raleigh** closely; while his score of 64.53 is encouraging, his 5% park penalty and the difficulty of the matchup demand high-volume production to justify the start over the depth currently sitting on our bench.",
